## Project: Sports Betting Decision Support

### Critical File Paths
- `picks.json` lives at `.agents/skills/bet-tracker/picks.json` — this is the ONLY source of truth for picks
- NEVER read/write from `.claude/skills/bet-tracker/` — that path is stale and unused
- Tracker CLI: `.agents/skills/bet-tracker/tracker.py` — always invoke with `python3`, NEVER `python`
- Dashboard URL hardcoded in `dashboard.html` at `const PICKS_URL` — update this if the picks.json path ever changes

### picks.json Rules
- NEVER edit picks.json manually — always go through the skills or tracker CLI
- Always `git pull` before reading picks.json and `git push` after writing it
- After any file reorganization, grep for `PICKS_URL` in dashboard.html to verify the path is still correct

### Python
- Use `python3` for all Python invocations

### Betting Concepts
- CLV (Closing Line Value) is the process signal; ROI is the outcome signal — both matter
- RLM threshold: 70%+ with actual line movement confirmation required
- Steam moves require 3+ books simultaneously — single-book moves are noise
- Primary edge: player props + cross-book line gaps
- Kelly sizing: use fractional Kelly (half-Kelly) to reduce variance
